Only YOU can change the way we vote at the European elections!

Last week, the four largest groups in the European Parliament found a deal to improve EU🇪🇺 elections:
🟣 all European citizens will be able to cast a truly pan-European vote: 28 seats will be reserved for European political parties and movements;
🟣 the European Parliament will better represent society: people identifying as women account for 51% of the population but represent only 38.9% of the members of Parliament. Using zipped lists and quotas, we can tackle this disparity;
🟣 all 18 year olds can become politicians no matter where they live;
🟣 voting will become easier, even if you live abroad;
🟣 EU countries will have to adapt their national rules to ensure the process to end up on the ballot is fair and democratic.

BUT it’s not over yet! 
The deal will be in effect only if the absolute majority of MEPs approve it AND all Member States have to ratify it.

To make sure your vote will matter in 2024, reach out to your MEP or join the I Vote Europe campaign - https://www.ivoteurope.eu/contact-your-mep

