The world is in the midst of a climate crisis, and what we need are no more empty promises but concrete plans for action.

Pollution-related causes led to one in every six premature deaths worldwide in 2015. Pollution is also one of the major risks for further losing biodiversity. The climate impact of urban environments, with a high concentration of pollutants, urgently demands further action to avoid greater degradation of our environment and our health.

Therefore, we need to:

👉 Promote the reuse, refurbishment and recycling of existing materials to avoid waste pollution;

👉 Examine the idea of a pollution tax;

👉 Commit to the United Nations Strategic Plan for Biodiversity 2011-2020;

👉 Support the development of stronger assessment systems for urban development in view of its impact on biodiversity;

