If we have learnt one thing from COVID, it is that we need to reform European healthcare systems.

A crucial aspect of our health systems is accessibility. Rural and urban environments do not offer similar services and access to health. We must work on this point to ensure equal availability of healthcare providers by:

👉 Setting up a European Health Express for rural areas or areas that don’t have good access to healthcare;

👉 Investing in new ideas like mobile clinics such as those used by the Red Cross or Lifeline Express;

👉 Ensure sufficient coverage of general practitioners and primary care units in economically challenged areas;

👉 Improving compensation for doctors in rural areas;

👉  Facilitating medical services to difficult-to-reach areas through e-health, and other measures.

If you want to know more about our plans for European healthcare, stay tuned for more content shortly!
