If we have learnt one thing from COVID, it is that we need to reform European healthcare systems.

If we reform European Healthcare systems, we must ensure a European wide provision of mental health care services by: 

👉 Providing quick access to mental healthcare professionals through patients’ GPs;

👉 Offering mental healthcare should via innovative e-health platforms, such as video consultations;

👉 Pushing governments to play an active role in promoting mental healthcare to lower the threshold for patients to seek mental healthcare and forward the de-stigmatisation of mental health problems;

👉 Working  to eliminate stigma and mystification around  mental illnesses like depression, and providing both early and continued support as well as preventative measures;

👉 Taking a holistic, “all of society approach” to mental health based on the WHO Action Plan. State interventions regulating the occupational conditions with respect to worker dignity, work-life balance, working hours, vacation time, and the flexibility. 

Measures should be set in place to inform the workforce, to give them support in cases of distress, and to monitor the enforcement of workplace guidelines.

